            <div class="about-content">
                <div class="about-text">
                    <p>Our journey began in 2011 when our founder, during her NYSC service at Ilesha General Hospital, discovered that true care extends beyond clinical treatment. What started as simple acts of providing toiletries to patients evolved into a lifelong calling.</p>
                    
                    <p>From dedicating her salary to help orphanage children and widows, to now empowering individuals with business grants and skills training across continents - our mission has always been clear: <strong>"Instead of giving people fish, we help them learn to fish."</strong></p>

                    <div class="vision-mission">
                        <div class="vm-card">
                            <h3>Our Vision</h3>
                            <p>To create a society where every vulnerable person has equal access to opportunities, support, and sustainable livelihood.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="vm-card">
                            <h3>Our Mission</h3>
                            <p>To empower widows, widowers, and the less privileged with financial support, skills training, and emotional assistance for long-term stability and dignity.</p>
                        </div>
